Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Individual' radio button from Sequences box on Page 03
And I select 'DWI' from 'Weighting' dropdown menu
And I go to Page 04 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' tab
And I click on 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Lesion CZ' from 'Finding' dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled
And 'Characterization III' tab is enabled

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'DCE-MRI negative' radio button is enabled
And 'DCE-MRI positive' radio button is enabled
And 'No penetration of pseudocapsule' radio button is enabled
And 'Penetration of pseudocapsule' radio button is enabled

When I select 'DCE-MRI negative' radio button
Then 'No early or simultaneous contrast enhancement compared to the adjacent tissue' radio button is enabled
And 'Diffuse contrast enhancement without a suspicious correlate in T2w and/or DWI' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal contrast enhancement in typical BPH nodes in T2w' is enabled

When I select 'Penetration of pseudocapsule' radio button
Then 'Broad-based pseudo capsule contact > 10 mm' radio button is enabled
And 'Rectoprostatic angle obliteration' is enabled
And 'Pseudocapsular bulging' is enabled
And 'Infiltration of adjacent structures' is enabled
And 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Pseudocapsular bulging' radio button
Then 'Spiculated' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Infiltration of adjacent structures' radio button
Then 'Seminal vesicles' checkbox is enabled
And 'Neurovascular bundle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rectum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Urinary bladder' checkbox is enabled
And 'External urethral sphincter' checkbox is enabled
And 'Membranous urethra' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Seminal vesicles' radio button
Then 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
And 'Altered internal structure' checkbox is enabled
And 'Focal or diffuse T2w signal reduction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enlarged ejaculatory duct with T2w signal reduction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Obliteration of the prostate-seminal vesicle angle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Direct infiltration (per continuitatem)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Neurovascular bundle' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Focal or diffuse T2w signal reduction' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Separate focal T2w signal reduction' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Neurovascular bundle' checkbox
Then 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
